    "description": "Return a file object associated with the socket. The exact returned type depends on the arguments given to makefile(). These arguments are interpreted the same way as by the built-in open() function, except the only supported mode values are 'r' (default), 'w', 'b', or a combination of those. The socket must be in blocking mode; it can have a timeout, but the file object’s internal buffer may end up in an inconsistent state if a timeout occurs. Closing the file object returned by makefile() w...",
